From d5bd7c475a91148ebb3b5b4d9122e6b9ebcabefc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 22:30:19 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix multi-day student placement bug

When adding the same student to sessions on different days, the second
placement was silently wiping the first. Root cause: rmFromSched(sid)
scanned every day and every car before placing the new slot, which is
wrong for students with sessionsPerWeek>1.

Fix:
- rmFromSched now takes an optional {onlyDay:d} scope
- Track dragSrc on dragstart so moving a placed student between days
  removes exactly that source slot, not every occurrence
- placeIn/tryPair/tryExtendPair/addToGroup/dropToPool clear only the
  drag source (if any) or scope cleanup to the target day
- placePickup also scopes its internal cleanup to the target day

Pool drags still scope to the target day so sessionsPerWeek=1 students
don't accidentally stack. Regression test added (test 24).
---
